author: The Leader staff
title: Cash-Rawleigh, Smith, Stewart propel Bath
text: Posted Oct. 13, 2015 at 8:18 PM Updated at 8:18 PM By The Leader staff Posted Oct. 13, 2015 at 8:18 PM BATH | The Bath Haverling boys cross country team notched three top-four finishes Tuesday to lead the Rams to wins against Wheatland-Chili (23-34) and Batavia Notre Dame (15-50) at Bath Country Club. Wheatland-Chili’s Alex Hogue placed first overall with a time of 17:22. The next three finishers were from Bath. Jordan Cash-Rawleigh of Bath placed second with a time of 18:24. Teammate Tyler Smith was third in 18:44 and Aaron Stewart finished fourth for the Rams in 18:54. Bath also got a sixth-place finish from Torrin Lisi (19:54) and an eighth-place showing from Corey Sprague (20:15). “I was pretty pleased for the most part,” Bath head coach Todd Ludden said. “My top three guys ran well for the competition that was there.” Bath’s top two girls finishers were Harley Mattison, who finished third in 24:10, along with Monet Harris, who posted an eighth-place time of 25:58. Bath (16-0) will run at the Alden Invitational Saturday. “It was a good solid effort and I’m looking forward to see how they run in Alden on Saturday,” Ludden said. By The Leader staff
